<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-12-10T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-12-10T16:00:00-05:00" n="414" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d414">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.01/149: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Mayer</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-12-10T16:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">December 10,
                                        1924—4 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>309. Your telegram No. 478, December 9, 5 p.m.</p>
                        <p>I am much gratified by this result, and approve your action with regard
                            to modifications of draft which seem entirely satisfactory.</p>
                        <p>Repeat the above to Tokyo as the Department’s number 207, together with
                            your 478, December 9, 5 p.m.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>